reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this desk for my Adult daughter for her Birthday. She plans to make this her makeup vanity. She said putting it together by herself was easy. It appears to be sturdy, the drawers are made of a cloth like bin fabric with a hard sturdy pull. Which was unexpected. Good height and nice size desk top. The 47inch top comes in 2 pieces.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Color grey is not grey
reviews.reviewText: The only issue I have, which I can absolutely get over for how little I paid for this product, is that the color grey isn't grey at all. It's obviously brown, and no I didnt get the one labeled brown on accident. Still a five star review as everything else is exactly like it said it'd be, and it even arrived earlier than expected. I did not have the issue with screws going through the top like some other people. If you use the right screws in the right spots, like the instructions tell you to, you wont have any issues. The instructions are insanely easy to follow. The size is smaller than I wanted, but I didn't look fully at the depth dimension, but 100% my fault. It's at a comfortable height for my chair (standard computer chair). Not for long term use I would think, but enough to get me though college I'm sure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price
reviews.reviewText: it’s the perfect size if you don’t have much space and just need a small workspace. It did come with a bit of paint on it that i can’t seem to scratch off. My only complaint is the drawers are felt and not wooden, they feel very flimsy and are smaller in person than they look in pictures. I thought they’d be wooden but I should have read the description, the hooks on the side are a nice addition. Overall for the price its a great desk. Set up in under an hour.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Functional and Affordable
reviews.reviewText: Cute little desk; perfect for a teen who just needs space for homework and laptop. I was able to put it together myself in less than an hour, and it’s quite sturdy. I highly recommend for anyone looking for a cheap and practical desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I bought this desk cause I am a beginner nail tech and I needed somewhere to work. I really like it! The drawers are not wood they are like felt material but they are still durable and nice!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: So I bought this desk for my 7 year old daughters room. We needed a smaller desk to fit in a smaller space. This had no reviews so I looked at the sellers page to make sure the other desks had reviews.Pros:It fits in a small spaceIt’s a good starter desk for small kids that will most likely ruin it sooner than later with markers and food fingerprintsCons:The drawers are deceiving in the photos. It makes you think you are getting regular wooden drawers. Well, only the front of the drawer is wooden. The actual drawer is fabric. Not happy about that.It’s made with cheap fake wood but it will do for now.Not that sturdy but as I said it will do for now.
